      "relevance": "The periodic event that resets the interior and produces altered survivors.",
      "body": "A periodic event in which the region's field briefly goes total. Onset is preceded by measurable attenuation of sound, wind, and wildlife activity (field term: *the hush*); instruments register a field drop earliest along the coastal ring (see [[Station 9]]). Onset affords minutes of warning.\n\n**Effect.** Survival among those caught is below ten percent; recorded outcomes include displacement, fusion with terrain, and partial subtraction of tissue. Surviving individuals are recovered presenting with Nonlocal Integration Syndrome.\n\n**Aftermath.** Each NCE reconfigures the interior: established paths, survey data, and anomalous site positions are rendered invalid. Displaced material and survivors are recovered at the perimeter under post-swell protocol.\n\n-------\n\n**AUDIO ASSESSMENT — FIELD RECORDING CR-7**\n*Recovered from CSD Officer [REDACTED] following NCE event, 3 Asmaand 891. Recording device recovered at perimeter under post-swell protocol. Subject unrecovered.*\n\n**Recording conditions.** Duration: 4 minutes, 38 seconds. Audio quality: severely degraded. Predominant content is consistent with NCE ambient field — subsonic resonance, atmospheric compression, and broadband noise at levels consistent with full-field onset. Voice content is present beneath ambient noise floor.\n\n**Identified vocalisation.** Analysts identified one phrase at 2 minutes, 14 seconds: *\"leave me alone.\"* Phrase is faint; identification confidence is assessed at moderate. Vocalisation is consistent with the subject's documented vocal profile. No further intelligible speech recovered.\n\n**Unidentified sounds.** Intermittent sounds of a wet, low-frequency character are present at 3 minutes, 02 seconds through 3 minutes, 41 seconds. Assessed as biological in origin. Source uncharacterised.\n\n**Assessment.** Recording is consistent with partial-exposure NCE experience. Vocalisation content is noted for the record; no interpretive weight is assigned. Unidentified biological sounds are flagged for review by the medical division.\n\n**Classification.** Filed under NCE casualty record. Cross-referenced: CR-7, post-swell recovery log, 3 Asmaand 891.",
