    {
      "code": "Σ-3",
      "title": "The Sleeping Bloom",
      "group": "BIOLOGICALS",
      "sub": "Class Σ (stillness) — flora, lethal",
      "fields": [
        [
          "CLASS",
          "Σ — stillness"
        ],
        [
          "HAZARD",
          "Lethal — induced stillness on inhalation"
        ]
      ],
      "body": "White-flowering plant found across highland and mid-band terrain, frequently in dense growth. Airborne compounds induce rapid onset motor stillness on inhalation. Effect is irreversible in all assessed cases; subjects are recovered in situ. Olfactory detection is possible at low concentrations; proximity sufficient for detection is assessed as proximity sufficient for effect onset. Sessile. Classified lethal.\n\n**FIELD RECOVERY REPORTS — Σ-3 ENCOUNTERS**\n\n**Case 03 // 22 Asmaand 886**\nSubject recovered standing, upright, in dense Σ-3 growth. Vital signs absent. No sign of struggle or repositioning; personal equipment undisturbed. Facial expression recorded as relaxed. Estimated time of entry: 2 hours prior to recovery. Post-mortem interval inconsistent with this estimate; assessed at 6–8 hours. Discrepancy unresolved.\n\n**Case 11 // 9 Nevelmaand 889**\nThree-person party. Two subjects recovered in situ within Σ-3 boundary; one recovered outside it. Outside subject reported no olfactory detection and no awareness of the other subjects having stopped. On debrief, reported only that the other two had fallen behind and had not answered.",
      "relevance": "",
      "media": {
        "images": [],
        "audio": []
      }
    },
    {
      "code": "Μ-2",
      "title": "The Caller",
      "group": "BIOLOGICALS",
      "sub": "Class Μ (mirror) — aquatic, lethal",
      "fields": [
        [
          "CLASS",
          "Μ — mirror"
        ],
        [
          "HAZARD",
          "Lethal — lures by mimicked voice"
        ]
      ],
      "body": "Aquatic organism present in the shallows of still pools. Produces vocal mimicry of the subject leaning over the pool surface. Contact is lethal.\n\n**FIELD RECOVERY REPORTS — Μ-2 ENCOUNTERS**\n\n**Case 04 // 7 Smeltmaand 887**\nTwo-person survey team at Ω-1 proximity. Subject A reported auditory mimicry of Subject B's voice originating from below the pool surface; Subject B simultaneously reported auditory mimicry of Subject A's. Both subjects moved toward the water. Subject B entered to knee depth before extraction. Subject B recovered. On debrief, Subject B reported the mimicked voice had accurately reproduced a statement Subject A had never made in their presence. Information source: uncharacterised.\n\n**Case 09 // 14 Bloeimaand 890**\nSubject recovered at pool edge, unresponsive. Evidence of partial submersion; no witness to entry. Vital signs absent. Body recovered intact. Circumstances unconfirmed; Μ-2 involvement assessed as probable.\n\n**Case 22 // 1 Rijpmaand 893**\nSubject recovered approximately 3m below pool surface. Subject had survived a prior Μ-2 encounter (see Case 04) and had been debriefed and cleared for field duty. On that debrief, subject reported the mimicked voice had used the name of a deceased family member. Entry into Ω-1 zone on this occasion was unsanctioned. Recovery of subject: unsuccessful.",
      "relevance": "",
      "media": {
        "images": [],
        "audio": []
      }
    }
